President Obama spoke with President Karzai to inform him of his decision to accept General Stanley McChrystal's resignation and to nominate General David Petraeus as the new commander of the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan. Both leaders praised General McChrystal's leadership and service. President Obama emphasized that this personnel change does not affect U.S. policy in Afghanistan or its commitment to Afghanistan's future. The President also stressed the importance of continued collaboration between the U.S. and Afghanistan to maintain momentum against the Taliban. President Karzai welcomed the nomination of General Petraeus and pledged his support for a successful transition.